}f dg =\sum_{k=1}^{n} f(x_k)\Delta g(x_k)$$where $\Delta g(x_n) = g(x_n^+)-g(x_n^-)> 0$. Let $(X, \mathcal{H}, \mu)$ be a measure space and let $f: X \rightarrow [0, \infty]$ be a  measurable function. We define the Lebesgue integral of $f$ over $X$ as $$\int_{X}f d \mu= \sup \left\{ \int_{X}g d \mu: 0 \le g \le f, g \,\, \text{is simple} \right\}.$$ I would be glad if a proof or correspondence can be given.
